CONTEXT MergeAlone IN ENGLISH
-- Negative test for the Stage-1 oscillation analysis.
-- A single uniqueness/merge rule. Merging strictly reduces the number of
-- atoms, so it always terminates on its own. The monotonicity refinement
-- must therefore NOT flag this rule with a (spurious) negative self-loop:
-- although the merge writes the concept E (which the rule reads via I[E]),
-- it deletes from `key` which occurs only POSITIVELY in `key;key~`, so a
-- delete cannot grow this rule's own violation set.

RELATION key[E*K] [UNI]

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS uniqueKey
RULE uniqueKey : key;key~ |- I[E]
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} MrgAtoms;E;", SRC I, TXT ";E;", TGT I )

POPULATION key CONTAINS [ ("e1","k1") ; ("e2","k1") ]
ENDCONTEXT
